</p>

<p class="jp">
        晴れた朝、雪の中の龍安寺の鏡容池。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Snow" /><category term="Ponds" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The Kyoyochi Pond at Ryoanji Temple, on a sunny morning in the snow.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01403_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01403_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Bamboo Path・雪の竹林</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250210/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Bamboo Path・雪の竹林" /><published>2025-02-10T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-10T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/bamboo-path</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250210/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        Morning in the Arashiyama Bamboo Grove after the snow.
</p>

<p class="jp">
        雪の後の嵐山竹林の朝。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Snow" /><category term="Bamboo Grove" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Morning in the Arashiyama Bamboo Grove after the snow.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01326_ai-2_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01326_ai-2_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ryoanji Snow Garden・龍安寺の雪庭</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250209/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ryoanji Snow Garden・龍安寺の雪庭" /><published>2025-02-09T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-09T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/snow-garden</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250209/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        The famous rock garden at Ryoanji Temple, covered with snow.
</p>

<p class="jp">
        雪に覆われた龍安寺の有名な石庭。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Snow" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Gardens" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The famous rock garden at Ryoanji Temple, covered with snow.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01369-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01369-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Arashiyama in the Snow</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250208/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Arashiyama in the Snow" /><published>2025-02-08T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-08T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/snow-in-arashiyama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250208/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
        Looking across the Oi River at fresh snow in the morning.
</p>

<p class="jp">
大堰川の向こう岸に朝の新雪を眺める。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Snow" /><category term="Katsura River" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking across the Oi River at fresh snow in the morning.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01305_ai-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01305_ai-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Rakushisha・落柿舎</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250207/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Rakushisha・落柿舎" /><published>2025-02-07T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-07T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/rakushisha</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250207/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
    Close up on a straw hat and raincoat, at the entrance to Rakushisha, the "Hut of Fallen Persimmons." The great 17th Century master of Haiku, Matsuo Basho, visited numerous times and wrote his famous diary "Saga Nikki," during one of his stays here.
</p>

<p class="jp">
楽只舎の入口にある麦藁帽子と雨合羽にクローズアップ。 
17世紀の俳句の偉大な巨匠、松尾芭蕉は何度もここを訪れ、有名な日記「嵯峨日記」を書いた。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Close up on a straw hat and raincoat, at the entrance to Rakushisha, the "Hut of Fallen Persimmons." The great 17th Century master of Haiku, Matsuo Basho, visited numerous times and wrote his famous diary "Saga Nikki," during one of his stays here.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_IMG_0950.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_IMG_0950.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Ogura Pond・小倉池</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250206/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ogura Pond・小倉池" /><published>2025-02-06T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-06T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/oguraike</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250206/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
    Blue sky reflects in the semi-frozen Ogura Pond.
</p>

<p class="jp">
  半凍結状態の小椋池に青空が映る。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Ponds" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Blue sky reflects in the semi-frozen Ogura Pond.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_IMG_0947.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_IMG_0947.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Hello Osaka!・大阪へよこそ！</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250205/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hello Osaka!・大阪へよこそ！" /><published>2025-02-05T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-02-05T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/osaka</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250205/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
It was a cold, clear morning, so I went to Shogunzaka Temple above Higashiyama with a long telephoto lens.</p>
<p class="en">
  Looking south at the more industrial area of Kyoto, you can see the Kamogawa River at left, and in the distance, the Osaka skyline. Among the buildings at lower right are the Nintendo’s headquarters.
</p>

<p class="jp">
寒い晴れた朝だったので、望遠レンズを持って東山の上にある将軍塚の展望台まで出かけた。
</p>
<p class="jp">
京都の工業地帯を南に見ると、左手に鴨川が見え、遠くに大阪のスカイラインが見える。右下のビル群の中に任天堂の本社がある。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Views" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[It was a cold, clear morning, so I went to Shogunzaka Temple above Higashiyama with a long telephoto lens. Looking south at the more industrial area of Kyoto, you can see the Kamogawa River at left, and in the distance, the Osaka skyline. Among the buildings at lower right are the Nintendo’s headquarters.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01164_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2502_A7R01164_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>